Afropop star, Tiwa Savage has wished her father were business magnate and Africa’s richest man, Aliko Dangote. The “Somebody’s Son” singer in a recent post lamented the many struggles people go daily to make ends meet.   Is Mummy GO Singer Olakira’s sister?     I’m not cool with God, says filmmaker Editi Effiong     No girl is a saint – Rapper Erigga   While Tiwa prayed for God’s continual intervention she wondered why she wasn’t fortunate to have Aliko Dangote as her father. The mother of one, who announced the demise of her father via her Instagram page on July 19, 2022, however prayed his soul rests on in peace. “I have one more meeting. It is not easy looking for money o. God help me, but why my papa no be Dangote or something like that (may his soul rest in peace though)”, she wrote.